                                    <desc type="AcquisitionNote">Note in the left margin.</desc>
                                    <q xml:lang="en">This book was brought from Abyssinia by Mr. 
                                        <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14353Edwards">W. Edwards, <t:roleName xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="rank">Captain</t:roleName>,
                                        </persName> Highland Transport Train. <date when="1868-06">June 1868</date>.</q>
                                </item>
                                <item xml:id="e2">
                                    <desc type="AcquisitionNote">A sheet of paper measuring 126 x 200mm has been pasted to the inside of the 
                                        back cover, with a description of the manuscript's provenance on both sides, stating, that it was taken by 
                                        <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14353Edwards"><t:roleName xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="rank">Captain</t:roleName> William W.
                                        Edwards</persName> 'of the Madras Cavalry, who held an appointment under Lord Napier'.</desc>
                                </item>
